  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Covering Children&apos;s Rights</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project focuses on 2 areas of need in rural Limpopo Province, South Africa: The need to educate adults and children on the rights of the child; and the need to provide blankets for warmth in the winter. Children who are infected or affected by HIV will be provided with a winter blanket that will contain key messages promoting the rights of children. South Africa is one of the worst affected countries in world with regards to HIV and AIDS, and no one carries the burden more than children do.</narrative>
  </description>
